{"id":210,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":210,"title":"Blood","subtitle":"","short_title":"Blood","uri":"/scriptures/bd/blood","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/blood.t1","order":".000.584"},[".title","Blood"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/blood.p1","order":".000.585"},"Regarded by the Israelites as the seat of the life or vital energy of all flesh (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/17.10-14"},"Lev. 17:10–14"],"). In Old Testament times blood was forbidden as food (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/9.4"},"Gen. 9:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/3.17"},"Lev. 3:17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/7.26-27"},"7:26–27"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/19.26"},"19:26"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/12.16,23"},"Deut. 12:16, 23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/15.23"},"15:23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/14.32-34"},"1 Sam. 14:32–34"],"), which restriction was continued in the Church in New Testament times, at the Jerusalem conference (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/15.20-29"},"Acts 15:20–29"],"). The atoning power of a sacrifice was in the blood because it was regarded as containing the life of the animal and because the sacrifice was a type of the great sacrifice who is Jesus Christ (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/17.11"},"Lev. 17:11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/9.22"},"Heb. 9:22"],"). The scripture says that “almost all things are by the law purged with blood; and without shedding of blood is no remission” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/9.22"},"Heb. 9:22"],"). Jesus worked out a perfect atonement by the shedding of His own blood (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-jn/1.7"},"1 Jn. 1:7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/5.9-10"},"Rev. 5:9–10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.16-19"},"Mosiah 3:16–19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/27.19-21"},"3 Ne. 27:19–21"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/45.4"},"D&C 45:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/76.69"},"76:69"],"). Joseph Smith, as have many other prophets, sealed his testimony with his blood that the righteous might be honored and the wicked might be condemned (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/6.9-10"},"Rev. 6:9–10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/135.6-7"},"D&C 135:6–7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/136.39"},"136:39"],")."],["div",{"id":"p2","uri":"/scriptures/bd/blood.p2","order":".000.586"},"Often a covenant was sealed with blood (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/15.9-18"},"Gen. 15:9–18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/24.8"},"Ex. 24:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/zech/9.11"},"Zech. 9:11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/26.28"},"Matt. 26:28"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/10.29"},"Heb. 10:29"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/13.20"},"13:20"],")."]]],"refs":null}
